{
    "analysis": "The Executor has loaded the four telemetry files and produced a compact summary. metric.csv contains 1900 rows spanning timestamps 1705757820–1705759260 and includes components such as carts, catalogue, orders, payment, user, and their DBs. KPI names present include cpu, mem, socket, diskio, latency-50, latency-90, workload, and error. trace.csv and error_logs.csv are empty. log.csv has 460 rows with log.error_count and log.row_count across similar components. Since traces are unavailable, metric + log analysis must determine the root cause. The next step is to compute global thresholds per component-KPI (P95 and P5) using the full metric series, then filter metric points within the incident window and find which component-KPIs exceed P95 (high anomalies) or fall below P5 (low anomalies). This will narrow candidate faulty components for further log inspection.",
